<P>
   COXNET WHEELS _ (EDS: This is the CoxNet WHEELS page for the
current week.)
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS 0907 _ If Plymouth is really is headed for the end
of its road, then the 1999 Breeze is a reasonably nice stopping
point. (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes
3-column color photo of 1999 Plymouth Breeze and a 18-pica color
photo of the car's interior.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: AT A GLANCE _ Fact box previewing the 1999 Plymouth
Breeze.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: THE MECHANIC _ Your vehicle's cooling system is a working
example of the rule of physics stating that heat will always move
toward a cooler area or object. The entire production depends on a
cast of supporting parts. If one of them falls down on the job, the
whole system suffers and your car overheats. (Carter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). Includes 1-column color photograph of
columnist.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ (Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   THE-MECHANIC _ (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
