</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS _ (EDS: This is the CoxNet WHEELS page for the
current week.)
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS 0907 _ If Plymouth is really is headed for the end
of its road, then the 1999 Breeze is a reasonably nice stopping
point. (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes
3-column color photo of 1999 Plymouth Breeze and a 18-pica color
photo of the car's interior.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: AT A GLANCE _ Fact box previewing the 1999 Plymouth
Breeze.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: THE MECHANIC _ Your vehicle's cooling system is a working
example of the rule of physics stating that heat will always move
toward a cooler area or object. The entire production depends on a
cast of supporting parts. If one of them falls down on the job, the
whole system suffers and your car overheats. (Carter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). Includes 1-column color photograph of
columnist.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ (Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   THE-MECHANIC _ (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   PERSONAL FINANCE
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ The best way to make money in the market is to stick
with big companies that have the power to grow even bigger, says
Fritz Meyer. The record of large growth funds tends to back him up.
Sort of. (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   TV-GETREAL _ Review of new Fox show, ``Get Real.'' (Kloer,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ As much as I loved looking at water lilies here
and there, still I did not go rushing to buy them. It wasn't time.
Recently, the time came. Gardening is funny that way: You enjoy a
plant for years, but not enough to want to grow it. Then, one day,
you just have to have it for your own. (May, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-CHILDREN _ Nurturing a love of gardening in children
begins by encouraging them to experience nature. For kids, that
experience often begins in their own back yards. Experts share
secrets on how to make gardening more inviting to children.
(Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
