distinctive homes that have played an important role in
Washington's social and diplomatic life. The 1999 tour will be held
Sept. 12 and includes visits to homes of former presidents,
ambassador's residences and the work of decorators and architects.
The tour is sponsored by the Friends of Wilson House, and benefits
the Woodrow Wilson House, Washington's only presidential museum.
Tickets are $20 on the day of the tour, and a pre-tour brunch and
lecture is also available for $39. For tickets call 202-387-4062,
ext. 18.
