<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PHILIP GLASS VAMPS ON `DRACULA' THEME 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Dracula'' _ The 1931 Bela Lugosi classic is
reissued with a soundtrack written by Philip Glass and performed by
the Kronos Quartet. It's effective, but so was the use of
Tchaikovsky's ``Swan Lake'' in director Tod Browning's original
release. Dwight Frye is terrific as Renfield, and the tape is only
$15.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Other Sister'' _ Director Garry Marshall was terrific with
comedy when he oversaw the TV series ``The Odd Couple'' and was a
producer of ``Happy Days.'' He even gave a fine acting performance
as the casino operator in Albert Brooks's ``Lost in America.'' But
his feature-film work, including this lame romantic comedy, has
been dreadful. Obvious. Dull. Insipid.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Last Days'' _ Filmmaker Jim Moll follows a handful of
Holocaust survivors back to the death camps. The result is dramatic
_ without being sentimental _ and powerfully understated. It was
produced in association with the Shoah Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Coalition for Quality Children's Media has hooked up with
the Internet site reel.com to disseminate its list of approved
children's videos. The KIDSFIRST program features reviews and
selections of current and classic children's videos.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: Get ``Analyze This'' on DVD. The outtakes are worth
the retail price. Stars Billy Crystal, who never shuts up, and
Robert De Niro, who hardly says a word, are terrific together. The
commentary audio track features director Harold Ramis's
observations about working with actors whose styles are so
different. . . . Buena Vista Home Video will begin releasing
classic Disney animation on DVD on Oct. 26 with ``Pinocchio''
leading the way. Disney could not have selected a better title,
since the detailed animation work is unsurpassed. Just check out
the carvings on the pool scene at Pleasure Island.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Sept. 14: ``Cookie's Fortune,'' ``Children
of Heaven,'' ``The Snow of Winter,'' ``The Prince of Egypt'' (DVD),
``All Creatures Great and Small,'' ``God Said, `Ha!' '' ``Children
of Heaven.'' Sept. 21: ``My Favorite Martian,'' ``Labyrinth,''
``Atomic Train,'' ``The Dark Crystal,'' ``Lulu on the Bridge.''
Sept. 28: ``The Mummy'' (DVD), ``Alvin and the Chipmunks Meet
Frankenstein,'' ``My Favorite Martian'' (DVD). Oct. 5: ``Lolita''
(1999 version), ``Scooby-Doo and the Witch's Ghost.'' Oct. 19:
``The Wizard of Oz'' (remastered and DVD). Oct. 31: ``The Blair
Witch Project.''
</P>
</TEXT>
