<P>
   CBS-VIACOM (Los Angeles) Will UPN be smacked down in the biggest
media merger in history? Though CBS and Viacom executives declined
to comment specifically on its fate, the three year old upstart
television network may face being sold or folded into CBS in the
wake of the agreement announced Tuesday for Viacom Inc. to buy CBS
Inc. in an all-stock transaction valued at $34.45 billion. By Marla
Matzer.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in the ``e'' entertainment, ``n'' California and
``a'' national news file.)
</P>
