Angeles City Council offered only a dim hope of keeping alive
prospects of a team being placed at the Los Angeles Memorial
Coliseum. The council voted to reject going to the public with a
vote on whether to use tax revenue from a football franchise to
improve parking around the Coliseum. By Rick Orlov and Steve
Dilbeck. (Will move in the ``s'' sports and ``n'' California news
file.)
