<P>
   BC-MARKET-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Sept. 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Sept.
1, about the daily performance of the stock market misstated the
composition of a secondary offering by Juniper Networks, whose
shares fell 12 percent last Wednesday. Of the 5.75 million shares
registered for the sale, more than half are coming from
shareholders, not from company officials.
</P>
