   (NYT2) UNDATED -- Sept. 7, 1999 -- JET-FIGHTER, 09-07 -- The aft
fuselage for the fourth F-22 flight-test aircraft is delivered from
Boeing to team partner Lockheed Martin, bottom. At top, the F-22.
Lockheed Martin is holding a pep rally in the Virginian suburbs on
Tuesday and Wednesday to pump up the top subcontractors of the F-22
program and send them off to lobby Congress this week, The rally is
part of the furious bid begun with Pentagon officials during the
vacation break to win back the money cut from the $70 billion
program. (Boeing/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) MILFORD, N.H. -- Sept. 7, 1999 -- QUAYLE-CAMPAIGN, 09-07
- Former Vice President Dan Quayle, campaigning for the Republican
presidential nomination, waits the start of a Labor Day parade
while surrounded by members of the St. Alfio's Band from Lawrence,
Mass., on Monday. These days, Quayle, whose slingshot career
allowed him to glimpse the heights and depths of American politics
before he turned 45, would seem to be at the bottom of his personal
trajectory. Yet he perseveres, with a poignant tenacity that he and
friends say is grounded in a dogged belief in the possibility of
his own political success and redemption. (Jared Leeds/New York
Times Photo) LITE
</P>
