   (NYT33) NEW YORK -- Sept. 7, 1999 -- TEN-USOPEN-4, 09-07 -- No.
5 seed Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil during his match against Magnus
Norman of Sweden at the U.S. Open on Tuesday. Norman had been about
to serve for the first set against Kuerten before what he later
described as ``unbelievable pain'' in his back slowed his step; he
retired after dropping the set, 7-6 (7-4). (Angel Franco/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT32) MASHHAD, Israel -- Sept. 7, 1999 -- ISRAEL-BOMBERS-3,
09-07 - Muhammad Krayim, 56, right, the brother of Nazal Krayim, an
Israeli-Arab who was killed in an apparent suicide-bombing attempt,
talks about his brother's death on Tuesday. ``This is the blackest
day of my life,'' said Krayim, a schoolteacher, as he sat in his
house with stunned relatives. ``In my worst nightmares I never
imagined such a thing. The whole family condemns this and we feel
ashamed.'' (Rina Castelnuovo/New York Times Photo)
