r f BC-LYCOS-LYCOS_SFCHRON &LR;      09-07 0339
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LYCOS-LYCOS </SLUG>
 _ SF CHRON  
 Lycos Adding Investment Content In $78.3 Purchase of Quote.com
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; By Deborah Solomon &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Copyright 1999 San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
Lycos plans to announce today that it is acquiring Quote.com of
Mountain View for $78.3 million in a deal that will add more
financial content to the Lycos Web site.
</P>
<P>
   Quote.com, which provides investment information such as stock
quotes, mutual fund information, earnings forecasts and company
profiles, will become part of the Lycos Network.
</P>
<P>
   Lycos, which is best known for its search engine, features other
content on its Web site from partners like Wired News, Suck.com and
MailCity.
</P>
<P>
   Ron Sege, executive vice president of Lycos of Waltham, Mass.,
said Quote.com will retain its name and its Web address but will
become the main provider of financial information on the Lycos Web
site.
</P>
<P>
   ``This brings Quote.com's premier investment information, as
well as its community and message information, to Lycos users and
brings Lycos' reach to Quote.com,'' Sege said.
</P>
<P>
   Lycos is among the five-most-visited sites on the Web, according
to Media Metrix. It has been trying to beef up its Web presence in
the face of competition from America Online, Microsoft and Yahoo.
Lycos and its competitors are trying to keep users coming back by
becoming one-stop-shops that offer everything from e-mail to news
to stock tips.
</P>
<P>
   With Quote.com under its belt, Lycos will also get access to
Quote.com's growing base of paid subscribers. In addition to free
financial content, Quote.com has a paid  &LR; subscription service that
allows users to access ``premium'' content and chart-making tools
that help investors track stocks. About 10,000 people subscribe to
the service, which costs from $25 to $100 per month.
</P>
<P>
   Sege said Quote.com will keep its headquarters in Mountain View
but said there may be some reshuffling of jobs after the purchase
closes. Quote.com would not disclose its number of employees.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service Clients) &QL;  &LR;
</P>
