<HEADLINE>
A CLOSER LOOK GORE'S PROPOSAL
</HEADLINE>
  (With GORE-HEALTH) 
 (nk) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Following are the main goals of a health-care proposal that Vice
President Al Gore outlined Tuesday in an address in Los Angeles:
</P>
<P>
   _ Guarantee access to affordable insurance for all children by
2005.
</P>
<P>
   _ Expand eligibility for the Children's Health Insurance Program
to include children in a family of four with an income of up to
$41,750.
</P>
<P>
   _ Let uninsured parents enroll in this program if their children
are eligible.
</P>
<P>
   _ Penalize states that fail to meet federal goals for insuring
children.
</P>
<P>
   _ Provide tax credits to help individuals and small businesses
buy health insurance.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
